FBIS4-62791 "drsov095_b_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-095 Daily Report 16 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Issues Gorbachev Seen Having `No Chances' in Presidential Vote Gorbachev Seen Having `No Chances' in Presidential Vote LD1605124794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1225 GMT 16 May 94 LD1605124794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] [Text] Moscow May 16 TASS -- Former Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev has no chances to become the Russian president as people do not support him, according to an influential lawmaker. "Statements by Mikhail Gorbachev about his possible participation in presidential elections in 1996 are completely groundless. He has no social basis", Viktor Mironov, deputy chairman of the Duma Committee on Security told TASS on Monday. "With all my respect to the former Soviet president, I believe he has exhausted his resources of a head of state", he added.
